=E2=80=93 because that is what Bechtel use. I can=E2=80=99t work out if =
this is actually the best course of action so I thought I would flag it =
to you to see if you have a view / the time and tech skills to dig into =
it further.

It looks to me like AWS SSO doesn=E2=80=99t achieve the ability for a =
user without an AWS account to SSO =E2=80=93 but I may be wrong.

So my plan was simply to buy Liquid=E2=80=99s time and work with them =
until Ping Identity is installed on the platform =E2=80=93 not great but =
I don=E2=80=99t have a better solution.

If I understand correctly, this is what the installation will look like:

*	We will create a new level of scheme security =E2=80=9CPingI=E2=80=9D=20
*	If a scheme is PingI the link in the review email will take the user =
to a login screen with a QR code provided by Ping Identity
*	User that has Ping Identity app on their phone holds smart phone up to =
screen, app verifies identity and sends message to us that we can let =
the participant in

I don=E2=80=99t really get the argument that this is a generic =
implementation =E2=80=93 surely different corporates use different SSO =
approaches / software and we will need to configure separately for each?

